<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-12 alert alert-info">
    Hello, <span id="User"><%= @conn.params["user"] %></span>! 
    Instructions
   1.	<b>Recommended:</b> Subscribe to users (other than default, i.e. user 1) before the simulation is started, to receive their tweets.
   2.	When the simulation is running (the tweet feeds is refreshing, user can try connect/disconnect button).
   3.	User can try querying for hashtags or mentions during or after the simulation.
   4.	Format for hashtags: #hashtag<random number> like #hastag10 or #hashtag555 (look in the feed for ones that actually exist)
   5.	Format for mentions: @user<user number> like @user15 or @user13 (look in the feed for ones that actually exist)
   6.	Tweet when the simulation is running, tweet will show up in the feed. (Use Ctrl + F if it scrolls to fast to see) 
   7.	To tweet or Query, input the exact text and press enter. Pls donâ€™t enter any extra spaces.
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8" style="overflow:scroll; height:400px;">
    <h3>Tweet Feed</h3>
    <ul id="TweetList" class="list-unstyled"></ul>
  </div>
  <div  class="col-md-4">
    <h4>Create Tweet</h4>
    <input type="text" id="NewTweet" placeholder="Type and press enter..." class="form-control">
    <h4>Query hashtag </h4>
    <input type="text" id="Qhashtag" placeholder="Type and press enter..." class="form-control">
    <h4>Query Mentions </h4>
    <input type="text" id="Qmentions" placeholder="Type and press enter..." class="form-control">
    <h4>Subscribe To </h4>
    <input type="text" id="Subscribe" placeholder="Type and press enter..." class="form-control">
    </br>
    <button type="button" id="Bconnect">Disconnect!</button>
  </div>
</div>